HEADWORD: Bluebeard
<hw>Blue"beard</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The hero of a
medi⟦ae⟧val French nursery legend, who, leaving home, enjoined his young
wife not to open a certain room in his castle. She entered it, and found
the murdered bodies of his former wives. -- Also used adjectively of a
subject which it is forbidden to investigate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>Bluebeard</qex> chamber of his mind, into which no eye
but his own must look.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bluebell</ent>⟦br⟧
